news.title: Can't tax flat's agreement & stamp duty value difference: ITAT
news.para: The tax tribunal held that a sum of Rs 24.3 lakh which was her share of the difference between the agreement value as per the allotment letter and the stamp duty value on the date of registration, which followed at a later date, cannot be taxed in her hands.

news.title: Accommodation with amenities is in the nature of hostel facilities, GST at 12% applies: AAR
news.para: On the same lines, as adopted earlier by the GST-AAR in other instances, notably, in the case of Bengaluru based Srisai Luxurious Stay and Noida based VS Institute and Hostel, the AAR held the provision of accommodation and services to be akin to that of a hostel or guest house which is subject to GST at 12%.

news.title: Mumbai-based builder booked for cheating flat buyer of Rs 3.3 crore
news.para: ​​The Amboli police on Tuesday booked the directors of Saisagar consultant Jayesh, his wife Shradda, his brother Deep Tanna and son Vivek Tanna for cheating and forgery.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government changes rules, developers can't build first & regularise later
news.para: In multi-storey buildings, developers until now could buy FAR in case of slight deviation from the sanctioned layout map.

news.title: NCLT Mumbai approves sale of Reliance Communications real estate assets
news.para: Resolution professional can sell assets of the company after submission of the resolution plan for approval by the tribunal, according to the order.

news.title: Two promoter entities offload 4.1% stake in Sunteck Realty for Rs 288 crore
news.para: According to the bulk deal data available with the BSE, Satguru Infocorp Services and Starlight Systems disposed of 30 lakh shares each, amounting to a 4.10 per cent stake in Sunteck Realty.

news.title: China pledges fresh support for property market
news.para: Beijing's top decision-makers, including President Xi Jinping, pledged at an annual closed-door meeting held Monday and Tuesday to "actively yet safely defuse risks in the real estate sector" and "meet the reasonable financing needs of real estate enterprises".

news.title: Country Garden has remitted funds to repay yuan bond in full
news.para: Bondholders of a total of 8 million notes, each with a principal of 100 yuan chose to exercise the put option by Nov. 28, while Country Garden has wired funds that fully repaid the principal and interest, the filing showed.

news.title: Greater Noida authority directs builders to resolve dispute with homebuyers
news.para: In a meeting of committee formed to resolve dispute between buyers and builders, the authority discussed the issue of completion of flats, formation of Apartments Owners Association (AOA), transfer of IFMS fund and registry of flats among others.

news.title: Suraj Estate Developers' Rs 400-crore IPO to open on December 18
news.para: Suraj Estate Developers' IPO is entirely a fresh issuance of equity shares worth Rs 400 crore with no Offer-for-Sale (OFS) component. Proceeds would be used towards the payment of debt availed by the company and its subsidiaries.

news.title: Police slap notice on Bengaluru-based builder over lake encroachment
news.para: Police said they served notice on the management of the private builder, directing its representatives to appear before them.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh: MPTB identifies land parcels to woo hotels for investment
news.para: Mandsaur, Mandu, Omkareshwar, Tamia, Parsili, Sanchi and Orchha have attracted investments from leading chains of hotels and resorts, said the board.

news.title: KDA meet for land purchase to develop Kanpur city township
news.para: The KDA officials requested the tenants to give a consent affidavit to sell their land to it for developing the New Kanpur City scheme.

news.title: Panchkula finishes drone survey of 619 slums
news.para: Gupta said work would have to be done in a time-bound manner to solve the problems of people living in Indira Colony, Rajiv Colony, Kharak Mangoli and other colonies.

news.title: Kolhapur civic body drive to clear building proposals
news.para: The KMC was informed by individual developers that the proposals that were earlier forwarded manually, are yet to be cleared despite the switchover to the online mode.

news.title: Yes Bank seeks buyers for Rs 4200 crore corporate and retail distressed loan book
news.para: Yes Bank has put some real estate developers for sale, such as ATS Realworth Pvt Ltd with debt of Rs 115 crore, ATS Infrastructure at 8 crore, ATS Township at Rs 26 crore, and Umritha Infrastructure at Rs 16 crore.

news.title: Enforcement directorate arrests another agent in Shine City fraud case
news.para: He was sent summons and asked to appear in Lucknow from where he was arrested after his credentials were verified and prima facie it was found that he had a hand in crime.

news.title: Kochi: Over Rs 11 crore fine collected from four stone quarries in November 2023
news.para: "Some have been imposed with a fine of Rs 2 to Rs 3 crore for the offence. There are some more quarries which are yet to remit the fine,” said a mining and geology department official.

news.title: NCLT admits IIFL Finance's claim against Satra Properties as financial debt
news.para: In 2022, the National Company Law Appellate Tribunal (NCLAT) had rejected a plea filed by the promoter of Satra Properties and upheld the ruling of the NCLT Mumbai bench to admit the company under the corporate insolvency resolution process (CIRP).

news.title: Bengaluru: Illegal buildings in town planning department's radar
news.para: Ward engineers too swamped with work, so BBMP takes away task of taking action against those who violate approved building plans from their hands
